Context
You're building a communication system for an emergency response team. Radio operators need to encode messages into Morse code for transmission over legacy equipment, and decode incoming Morse signals back to readable text.

Task
Implement two functions that translate text to Morse code and vice versa.

Requirements
Implement text_to_morse(text: str) -> str to convert plain text to Morse code
Implement morse_to_text(morse: str) -> str to convert Morse code back to text
Support letters A-Z (case insensitive) and digits 0-9
Use standard International Morse Code (dictionary provided)
Separate letters with single spaces
Separate words with / (space-slash-space)
Return empty string for empty input
Constraints
Input text contains only letters, numbers, and spaces
Morse code input uses . for dots and - for dashes
All input is valid (no error handling required for invalid characters)
Input strings are at most 1000 characters
Examples
Example 1: Basic Word
Input:

text_to_morse("SOS")
Output:

"... --- ..."
Explanation: S=..., O=---, S=..., separated by spaces.

Example 2: Multi-Word Message
Input:

text_to_morse("HELLO WORLD")
Output:

".... . .-.. .-.. --- / .-- --- .-. .-.. -.."
Explanation: Words are separated by /.

Example 3: Decoding
Input:

morse_to_text("... --- ...")
Output:

"SOS"
Explanation: Each Morse pattern maps back to its letter.